# Supabase Table and Admin Panel Management Guide

## Adding New Tables to Supabase

### 1. Database Schema Creation
When adding new tables to Supabase:

```sql
-- Example table structure following the established pattern
CREATE TABLE new_table_name (
  id UUID PRIMARY KEY DEFAULT gen_random_uuid(),
  name TEXT NOT NULL,
  description TEXT,
  is_active BOOLEAN DEFAULT true,
  sort_order INTEGER DEFAULT 0,
  created_at TIMESTAMP WITH TIME ZONE DEFAULT timezone('utc'::text, now()) NOT NULL,
  updated_at TIMESTAMP WITH TIME ZONE DEFAULT timezone('utc'::text, now()) NOT NULL
);

-- Add RLS (Row Level Security) policies
ALTER TABLE new_table_name ENABLE ROW LEVEL SECURITY;

-- Create policies for different access levels
CREATE POLICY "Allow public read access" ON new_table_name
  FOR SELECT USING (is_active = true);

CREATE POLICY "Allow admin full access" ON new_table_name
  FOR ALL USING (auth.jwt() ->> 'role' = 'admin');
```

### 2. Related Tables Pattern
For tables with relationships (like category_filters, category_embed_params):

```sql
-- Related table following the established pattern
CREATE TABLE new_table_related (
  id UUID PRIMARY KEY DEFAULT gen_random_uuid(),
  new_table_id UUID REFERENCES new_table_name(id) ON DELETE CASCADE,
  key TEXT NOT NULL,
  value TEXT,
  created_at TIMESTAMP WITH TIME ZONE DEFAULT timezone('utc'::text, now()) NOT NULL
);
```

## Server Component Pattern

### 3. Create Server Component
Following the pattern in [CategoryFilter.tsx](mdc:app/components/CategoryFilter.tsx):

```typescript
// app/components/NewTableFilter.tsx
import { createClient } from "@/utils/supabase/server";
import NewTableFilterClient from "./NewTableFilterClient";

export default async function NewTableFilter() {
  const supabase = await createClient();
  const { data: items } = await supabase
    .from("new_table_name")
    .select(`
      *,
      new_table_related (*)
    `)
    .eq("is_active", true)
    .order("sort_order", { ascending: true });

  return <NewTableFilterClient initialItems={items || []} />;
}
```

